Vice President Mike Pence delivered a speech at the 80th Annual Dinner of the Tax Foundation in Washington, D.C. He thanked the organization for its support and emphasized the importance of tax cuts and tax reform in stimulating economic growth. Pence highlighted the actions taken by the Trump administration to roll back government regulations and promote American energy. He also outlined the three principles of the administration's tax reform plan: cutting taxes for working families, simplifying the tax code, and making American businesses competitive. Pence urged the audience to support the passing of the largest tax cut in American history.